meaningMnemonic: A <kanji>branch</kanji> <kanji>bean</kanji> doesn't mean a whole lot this way, but you probably know the food that this describes anyways. This is <vocabulary>edamame</vocabulary>, a food made from <vocabulary>steamed soybeans</vocabulary>, usually with a bit of salt added for flavor.
readingMnemonic: The readings are the kun'yomi readings of the two kanji, unfortunately. That's the vocab words 枝 and 豆 combined into one.
